@startuml orchestrators-module-detail
title "Orchestrators Module - Workflow Coordination (Single Responsibility)"

!define ACCENTCOLOR #4A90E2
!define ORCHESTRATORCOLOR #F0E6FF
!define SRPCOLOR #E8F8F5

skinparam style strictuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFACD
skinparam NoteBorderColor #FFD700
skinparam ClassBackgroundColor #F5F5F5
skinparam ClassBorderColor ACCENTCOLOR

' Command Orchestrator
package "Command Execution Orchestrator" {
    class CommandOrchestrator #ORCHESTRATORCOLOR {
        --
        + new(): Self
        + handle_command(
            cmd: &str,
            args: &[String],
            original_input: Option<&str>,
            state: &mut TerminalState,
            ui: &mut TerminalUI
          ): Result<()>
        - handle_clear_command(state, ui): Result<()>
        - handle_reload_aliases_command(state): Result<()>
        - handle_command_not_found(cmd, state)
        - execute_and_display(cmd, args, original_input, state): Result<()>
        --
        **Single Responsibility**: Orchestrate command execution workflow
        **async/await**: Uses tokio for non-blocking execution
    }

    note right of CommandOrchestrator
        **Command Execution Workflow**:
        1. Check for special built-in commands:
           - "clear" → clear output buffer
           - "reload-aliases" → reload system + user aliases
        2. Verify command exists:
           - Skip if shell builtin (no PATH check)
           - Skip if history expansion (!!)
           - Skip if using original_input (shell syntax)
           - Otherwise: Check command_exists() cache
        3. If not found, show user-friendly error
        4. Otherwise, execute and display output
        5. Update TerminalState with output
        6. Re-render TerminalUI
    end note

    note bottom of CommandOrchestrator
        **Key Behaviors**:
        - Auto-install workflow NOT executed (M1 limitation)
        - Preserves shell operators via original_input
        - Blocks interactive commands (TTY-requiring)
        - Integrates with CommandExecutor
        - Updates terminal state for UI refresh
    end note
}

' Natural Language Orchestrator
package "Natural Language Orchestrator" {
    class NaturalLanguageOrchestrator #ORCHESTRATORCOLOR {
        - llm_client: Arc<dyn LLMClientTrait>
        - renderer: ResponseRenderer
        --
        + new(
            llm_client: Arc<dyn LLMClientTrait>,
            renderer: ResponseRenderer
          ): Self
        + handle_query(
            query: &str,
            state: &mut TerminalState,
            ui: &mut TerminalUI
          ): Result<()>
        - handle_success(response: String, state, ui)
        - handle_error(error: String, state, ui)
        --
        **Single Responsibility**: Orchestrate NL query workflow
        **Dependency injection**: LLM client + renderer
    }

    note right of NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
        **Natural Language Query Workflow**:
        1. Display "Querying AI assistant..." message
        2. Render TUI to show waiting state
        3. Query LLM with user input
        4. On success:
           - Render markdown response
           - Format with syntax highlighting
           - Add to output buffer
        5. On error:
           - Display user-friendly error
           - Suggest alternative actions
        6. Re-render TUI
    end note

    note bottom of NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
        **LLM Integration**:
        - Supports multiple LLM clients via trait
        - MockLLMClient for testing/development
        - HttpLLMClient for production (endpoint TBD)
        - ResponseRenderer handles markdown + syntax highlighting
        - No context passing (M2/M3 feature)
    end note
}

' Tab Completion Handler
package "Tab Completion Handler" {
    class TabCompletionHandler #ORCHESTRATORCOLOR {
        --
        + new(): Self
        + handle_tab_completion(state: &mut TerminalState)
        - complete_command(partial: &str): Vec<String>
        - complete_file(partial: &str): Vec<String>
        --
        **Single Responsibility**: Orchestrate tab completion workflow
    }

    note right of TabCompletionHandler
        **Tab Completion Workflow**:
        1. Extract current word from input buffer
        2. Determine completion context:
           - If no space before: Complete command
           - If space exists: Complete file path
        3. Get completions via CompletionProvider
        4. Show suggestions to user:
           - Display first N completions
           - Auto-complete if only one match
           - Show ambiguous matches
        5. Update input buffer
        6. Re-render TUI
    end note

    note bottom of TabCompletionHandler
        **M1 Limitations**:
        - No bash/zsh integration
        - No context-aware suggestions
        - No cached completions (Deferred to M2/M3)
    end note
}

' Supporting Components
package "Supporting Services" {
    interface LLMClientTrait <<trait>> {
        + query(text: &str): Result<String>
        + query_with_context(text: &str, context: Option<String>): Result<String>
        + query_with_history(text: &str, history: &[String]): Result<String>
    }

    class ResponseRenderer {
        + render_markdown(response: &str): Vec<String>
        + highlight_code(code: &str, language: &str): String
    }

    class CommandExecutor {
        + execute(cmd: &str, args: &[String], original_input: Option<&str>): CommandOutput
    }

    class PackageInstaller {
        + detect_package_manager(): Option<Arc<dyn PackageManager>>
        + install(package: &str): Result<()>
    }

    class CompletionProvider {
        + complete_command(partial: &str): Vec<String>
        + complete_file(partial: &str): Vec<String>
    }

    class TerminalState {
        + output: OutputBuffer
        + input: InputBuffer
        + history: CommandHistory
        + mode: TerminalMode
    }

    class TerminalUI {
        + render(state: &TerminalState): Result<()>
    }
}

' Message Formatter
package "Message Formatting" {
    class MessageFormatter {
        + command(input: &str): String
        + error(message: &str): String
        + success(message: &str): String
        + info(message: &str): String
        + warning(message: &str): String
        + banner_line(text: &str): String
        --
        Formats messages with ANSI colors
        for terminal display
    }
}

' Relationships
CommandOrchestrator --> CommandExecutor
CommandOrchestrator --> PackageInstaller
CommandOrchestrator --> TerminalState
CommandOrchestrator --> TerminalUI
CommandOrchestrator --> MessageFormatter

NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> LLMClientTrait
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> ResponseRenderer
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> TerminalState
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> TerminalUI
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> MessageFormatter

TabCompletionHandler --> CompletionProvider
TabCompletionHandler --> TerminalState
TabCompletionHandler --> TerminalUI

ResponseRenderer --> "ResponseRenderer"
LLMClientTrait --> "LLMRequest/Response"

' Architecture note
note top of CommandOrchestrator
    **Orchestrator Pattern** (Single Responsibility):
    Each orchestrator handles ONE workflow type:
    - CommandOrchestrator: Shell command execution
    - NaturalLanguageOrchestrator: LLM queries
    - TabCompletionHandler: Tab completion

    Benefits:
    - Separation of concerns
    - Easier to test individual workflows
    - Easy to add new workflows
    - Keeps main.rs clean and focused
end note

note bottom of CommandOrchestrator
    **Call Site** (in main.rs handle_event):
    - InputType::Command → CommandOrchestrator::handle_command()
    - InputType::NaturalLanguage → NaturalLanguageOrchestrator::handle_query()
    - TerminalEvent::TabComplete → TabCompletionHandler::handle_tab_completion()
end note

' Integration points
note right of TerminalState
    **State Mutation**:
    All orchestrators receive:
    - &mut TerminalState: Add output, change mode
    - &mut TerminalUI: Re-render after changes

    State updates trigger re-rendering
    for immediate visual feedback
end note

' Error handling note
note bottom of NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
    **Error Handling Strategy**:
    1. Network timeout → Show user message
    2. Invalid response format → Show error
    3. LLM service down → Show fallback
    4. Authentication error → Show helpful hint
    All errors caught and displayed gracefully
end note

@enduml
